<center>
   <br><br>
   <h1>Declarations</h1>
   <br>
</center>
<font size=4>
<ul>
   <li>Declarations are used to declare methods or variables that are
initialized within a page and are accessible to other scriptlets,
expressions, and declarations.</li>
   <li>They are defined as global and are not permitted to write to a
page.</li>
</ul>
<br><br>
<p>Example of a declaration:</p>
<font color="red">
   <p>&lt%! 
   <br>public java.util.Data PrintDate()
   <br>{
   <br>return(new java.util.Date());
   <br>}
   <br>%></p>
</font>
<br>
<p>This declaration can now be used by an expression in order to print the
date to the page:</p>
<font color="red">
   <p>The current date is:
      <br>&lt%= PrintDate() %></p>
</font>
</font>
</html>

